<TITLE> Blatter promises to help BFF </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 29 (bdnews24.com) - FIFA president Joseph S. Blatter promised newly elected Bangladesh Football Federation president Kazi Salahuddin all kinds of help to develop Bangladesh football. The FIFA boss met the three-member BFF delegation Tuesday before the three-day FIFA congress in Sydney Wednesday. The BFF president along with its senior vice president Abdus Salam Murshidi and vice president Manzoor Hossain Malu went to Sydney to attend the FIFA congress. BFF acting president Badal Roy said that the FIFA president talked to the Bangladesh delegation for one and a half hours and the meeting was an effective one. "I had a talk with Mr Salam by phone and he told me that the FIFA president had promised them all kinds of assistance in a bid to develop Bangladesh's football," Roy said quoting Salam. Kazi Salahuddin on May 20 met Asian Football Confederation (AFC) president Mohamed Bin Hammam, who promised to the BFF president to introduce him to Blatter in FIFA congress. 
